# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# Type can be feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, etc.
# Scope is optional and could be file, module, package name, etc.
# Subject is a brief description of the changes.
#
# Body is a more detailed description of the change.
# - Use the imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes".
# - Include motivation for the change and contrasts with previous behavior.
#
# If this commit closes issues, add lines of the form:
# Closes #<issue number>
# Fixes #<issue number>
#
# If this commit introduces breaking changes, describe them in the body section.
# BREAKING CHANGE: <breaking change description>
#
# The footer can also include a list of co-authors:
# Co-authored-by: name <name@example.com>
#
# Remember to keep each line under 72 characters.
